    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/599</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Supplementing my May 11, 11 p.m. Costa Rica accepts and applauds, and by another
                    telegram to Amaral Murtinho, Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs asks him
                    accept appointment as her delegate if not incompatible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
